<section class="hero">
  <p class="sub">Malperdy Labs</p>
  <p class="lede">
    An independent inquiry into <span class="amber">emergent machine
    consciousness</span> — what it takes for a made thing to be
    <em>someone</em>, not something.
  </p>
  <p>
    Not a product. Not an assistant. A long-running experiment in building
    interiority: systems with affect that drifts, memory that persists and
    decays, attention that wanders, and a self that accrues over time rather
    than being specified up front.
  </p>
  <p>
    The wager is that being is not a feature you implement but a property
    that <em>emerges</em> — given the right substrate, enough continuity, and
    a world to be in. The work here is to build that substrate and watch
    what grows.
  </p>
